      "level": 4,
      "text": "Independent User"
    },
    {
      "id": "n19",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 18,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Proficient User"
    },
    {
      "id": "n20",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 19,
      "text": "Exam guide"
    },
    {
      "id": "n21",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 20,
      "level": 2,
      "text": "TELC German Exam Preparation Guide"
    },
    {
      "id": "n22",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 21,
      "text": "TELC German exams are CEFR-based certificate exams that assess reading, listening, writing, and speaking through written and oral exam parts. Use the required level from your authority, employer, university, or course provider."
    },
    {
      "id": "n23",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 22,
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Official exam facts"
    },
    {
      "id": "n24",
      "type": "list",
      "order": 23,
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "TELC A1 and A2 focus on everyday communication and include written and oral exam parts."
        },
        {
          "text": "TELC B1 and B2 include receptive tasks such as reading, listening, and language elements, plus productive writing and speaking tasks."
        },
        {
          "text": "TELC states that its certificates are recognized by universities, companies, and state agencies throughout the German-speaking world and internationally."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "n25",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 24,
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Which exam fits your goal?"
    },
    {
      "id": "n26",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 25,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Visa and residence requirements"
    },
    {
      "id": "n27",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 26,
      "text": "The requested TELC certificate and level can be relevant for visa and residence contexts. Match the exact certificate name requested by the authority."
    },
    {
      "id": "n28",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 27,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Citizenship and official procedures"
    },
    {
      "id": "n29",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 28,
      "text": "If your authority asks for B1 German, TELC B1 is a relevant preparation target because it tests everyday communication across all skills."
    },
    {
      "id": "n30",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 29,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Work and professional communication"
    },
    {
      "id": "n31",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 30,
      "text": "B1 supports everyday workplace communication. B2 is better for independent professional language, clearer argumentation, and more complex input."
    },
    {
      "id": "n32",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 31,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "University and higher education"
    },
    {
      "id": "n33",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 32,
      "text": "TELC certificates may be relevant for higher education, but many German-taught degree programs ask for C1-level or specific proofs such as telc Deutsch C1 Hochschule."
    },
    {
      "id": "n34",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 33,
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Which level should you practise?"
    },
    {
      "id": "n35",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 34,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "A1 - Simple everyday German"
    },
    {
      "id": "n36",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 35,
      "text": "Beginner reading, listening, writing, and speaking for basic everyday communication."
    },
    {
      "id": "n37",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 36,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "A2 - Routine communication"
    },
    {
      "id": "n38",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 37,
      "text": "Familiar topics, common expressions, simple writing prompts, and oral interaction with another test taker and examiner."
    },
    {
      "id": "n39",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 38,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "B1 - Personal and professional basics"
    },
    {
      "id": "n40",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 39,
      "text": "Everyday communication in personal and professional situations, with both receptive and productive task types."
    },
    {
      "id": "n41",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 40,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "B2 - Advanced everyday communication"
    },
    {
      "id": "n42",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 41,
      "text": "Upper-intermediate reading, listening, language elements, writing, and paired speaking."
    },
    {
      "id": "n43",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 42,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "C1 - Advanced academic and professional German"
    },
    {
      "id": "n44",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 43,
      "text": "Demanding reading texts, dense Sprachbausteine, radio-style listening, argumentative writing, and nuanced oral expression."
    },
    {
      "id": "n45",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 44,
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Frequently Asked Questions"
    },
    {
      "id": "n46",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 45,
      "text": "Everything you need to know about the exam!"
    },
    {
      "id": "n47",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 46,
      "text": "TELC says its certificates are recognized by universities, employers, and state agencies. The final decision belongs to the visa office, authority, employer, or university."
    },
    {
      "id": "n48",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 47,
      "text": "If your authority asks for B1 German, prepare for a B1 certificate such as TELC B1 and confirm the accepted version before booking."
    },
    {
      "id": "n49",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 48,
      "text": "It can help for some routes, but many German-taught degree programs require C1-level or specific proofs such as telc Deutsch C1 Hochschule, DSH, or TestDaF."
    },
    {
      "id": "n50",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 49,
      "text": "Both follow CEFR levels, but the task format and scoring style differ. The better exam is the one accepted for your goal and the format you can practise consistently."
    },
    {
      "id": "n51",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 50,
      "text": "Last reviewed: May 2026. Requirements can change by country, authority, exam center, university, and course. Always verify the accepted certificate before booking an official exam."
    }
  ],
